TITLE: Disabling User Mode ASLR in Linux Guest (sh)
DESCRIPTION: Provides a command to disable address space layout randomization for user processes in Linux, which is required for reliable introspection in a PANDA guest. Needs sudo privileges and /proc filesystem support in the guest. Output is that ASLR is turned off for all user programs in the running Linux environment.
SOURCE: https://github.com/panda-re/panda-ng/blob/main/plugins/osi_linux/README.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
echo 0 | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/randomize_va_space
```

